<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1325,359,1905]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[312,418,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Breeding</emphasis>
: Both series of specimens were taken from common weeds. This suggests not only that this thrips is likely to be polyphagous but that it is probably not endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[264,371,1879,1905]" name="Australia" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Australia</collectingCountry>
and is likely to be found in South 
<collectingCountry box="[775,890,1879,1905]" name="China" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">East Asia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
